            <thetext>The spec for `getCurrentTimestamp` checks for a returned JSON object with 2 properties, but it doesn&#39;t say what names to use for the properties. This information is necessary to write a compliant server.

I looked at what a few contrib projects are doing in regards to this; RpcConsole&#39;s tests don&#39;t check the returned value (commented out), and the RpcExample application in contrib looks for:

{&quot;now&quot;: &lt;timestamp&gt;, &quot;json&quot;: &lt;qooxdoo_date&gt;}</thetext>
